[1] USA (Mississippi)
Date: Tue 23 Sep 2014
Source: Hattiesburg American, AP (Associated Press) report [summ., edited]
http://www.hattiesburgamerican.com/story/news/2014/09/23/mississippi-enterovirus-case/16098969/


Mississippi health officials have confirmed the state's 1st case of a virus that causes respiratory illness in children. The Mississippi State Department of Health on Tuesday [23 Sep 2014] confirmed a case of enterovirus D68 in Hancock County. Health officials say the child was hospitalized and has since recovered. Enterovirus D68 [EV-D68] is a more virulent strain of the virus that causes the common cold. It has shown up in 22 other states since mid-August [2014]. The virus can cause mild to severe illness, with the worst cases needing life support for breathing difficulties. Children with asthma are more vulnerable. No deaths have been reported.

