[Enterovirus D68 is now widespread throughout North America and continues to be associated with relatively mild disease and confined to children in their early years. The number of cases in some situations has been affected by extraneous factors such as closure of schools in British Columbia which has affected the date of 1st admission to school. The extent of the exposure to human enterovirus D68 suggests that the virus has been present in previous years, but not at a level greater than other infections in children. - Mod.CP

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2802168,106.]
